other_tests.findings: The exercise test showed a reduced maximum workload of 80 W (normal value: 234 Â± 110 W) and a reduced maximal oxygen uptake of 18 mL/kg/min (normal value: 35 to 45 mL/kg/min). Baseline plasma lactate values ranged from 1.0 to 2.2 mmol/L, and maximal exercise at 80 W evoked an increase in plasma lactate to 8.1 and 11.2 mmol/L.
Histology of a needle biopsy from the vastus lateralis muscle showed widespread subsarcolemmal accumulation of mitochondria in more than 5% of the muscle fibers.
